y, practice and research in a range of rural settings - from the experiences of gypsy traveller children in schools to attempts to encourage black and minority ethnic visitors to National Parks and contributes towards establishing the 'rural-ethnicity-nation' relationship as a key consideration on political and policy agendas. The new countryside? is essential reading for students, academics and researchers in a wide range of disciplines including: sociology; geography; social policy; and cultural, rural and environment studies. It will also be an invaluable resource for practitioners and policy makers across a wide range of sectors and services.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2023) 0aMarginality, SocialzGreat Britain. 0aMinoritieszGreat Britain. 0aSociology, RuralzGreat Britain. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / General.2bisacsh1 aAgyeman, Julian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAgyeman, Julian, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aAskins, Kye, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBhopal, Kalwant, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aConnolly, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDhillon, Perminder, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGardner, Hannah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHetherington, Kevin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNeal, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNeal, Sarah, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRobinson, Vaughan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSolomos, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 